@node Descr "Description"

Description
-----------

   MonSync is a small program which allows you to change those monitor drivers
parameters which are unsettable via their options/tooltypes, specifically
horizontal and vertical sync start and stop values.  Ever used MonEd, program
designed to adjust the monitor settings?  You know then, you can't save all
values.  This is where MonSync comes handy.

   I wrote it because the C= 1942 monitor, which I have, has no automatic
vertical resize, so Super72 modes look shrunk.  With MonEd, I found they can be
made fit whole screen by altering the sync parameters.

   Well, I wrote it at the occasion over year ago...  but as it did the job for
me, I forgot about it and not released :) My friend asked me about such
problem, so I finally wrote this doc, did some improvements, and released it.
Hope you find it useful, too.

See @{"usage" link Usage}.

@endnode

@node Require "Requirements"

Requirements
------------

    Requires at least Kickstart 2.04 (v37).
    NOTE: Tested only under 3.0/3.1.

@endnode

@node Usage "Usage"

Usage
-----

   MonSync can be used only from Shell.  Will crash if launched from Workbench.
Probably you will want to call it from startup-sequence/user-startup.

   Options template:

   MONITOR,HSSTRT/K,HSSTOP/K,VSSTRT/K,VSSTOP/K,REFRESH/S,LIST/S,HELP/S:

        MONITOR <name>          Name of the monitor. '.monitor' suffix
                                is optional. Note, monitor names are
                                case-sensitive!

        HSSTRT/K                Horizontal sync start value
        HSSTOP/K                Horizontal sync stop value
        VSSTRT/K                Vertical sync start value
        VSSTOP/K                Vertical sync stop value

                                As those found in MonEd. Values can be
                                decimal or hexadecimal. The latter must
                                be prefixed with '$' or '0x'.

        REFRESH/S               If specified, the display will be
                                immediatelly refreshed. Usually not needed,
                                if you call MonSync in user-startup.
                                
        LIST/S                  List available monitors.

        HELP/S                  Display brief usage info.

@endnode

